I&#x27;ve never actually used TypeScript until today, but just the tutorial code takes forever to compile, this snippet took 2 seconds for example, whaaat??<p><pre><code>    interface Person {
        firstname: string;
        lastname: string;
    }

    function greeter(person: Person) {
        return &#x27;Hello, &#x27; + person.firstname + &#x27; &#x27; + person.lastname;
    }

    var user = {firstname: &#x27;John&#x27;, lastname: &#x27;Doe&#x27;}

    document.body.innerHTML = greeter(user);
</code></pre>
It&#x27;s a shame really, because it looks like a really cool project.
